From: Brian Norris <briannorris@chromium.org>
Date: Thu, 10 Mar 2016 15:47:26 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] Support placing RW configuration separately from ServerRoot

cupsd writes out its printer data to
$ServerRoot/{printers.conf,ppd/*.ppd}, alongside less volatile data,
like cupsd.conf and cups-files.conf. Some systems might like to keep the
static config files (i.e., ServerRoot) protected in a read-only
partition, while placing the volatile printer info in a writeable
partition.

Support that with a new conf directive, PrinterRoot. If not supplied,
PrinterRoot defaults to ServerRoot.

Patch supplied upstream here:
https://www.cups.org/str.php?L4783

Signed-off-by: Brian Norris <briannorris@chromium.org>
---
